Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria, indicating possible nephropathy. Urine is abnormal in appearance, color, and specific gravity, supporting renal involvement. Low HbA1c and normoglycemia may reflect recent changes in glucose metabolism or possible malnutrition. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying causes of renal impairment.
